[14:15:58.282] [INFO ] ── RAW ANSWER ──
[14:15:58.283] [INFO ]     As of the latest **NovaAI Employee Handbook (v3.2, updated June 1, 2024)**, the on-call compensation rates are as follows:
    
    - **Standard On-Call Rate**: **$50/hour** for hours spent actively responding to incidents while on call.
    - **Standby On-Call Rate**: **$25/hour** for being available but not actively engaged in incident response (e.g., carrying a pager but not working).
    - **Weekend/Holiday Premium**: An additional **$25/hour** (stacks with the above rates) for on-call shifts falling on weekends or NovaAI-recognized holidays (e.g., Christmas Day, New Year’s Day).
    
    ### Key Details:
    1. **Eligibility**: Applies to all full-time employees (FTEs) and contractors (with ≥6 months tenure) in roles requiring on-call duties (e.g., Engineering, DevOps, SRE teams).
    2. **Payment Timing**: Compensation is processed in the payroll cycle following the on-call period (e.g., on-call hours in June are paid with the July 15 paycheck).
    3. **Taxation**: Rates are **pre-tax** (subject to local tax laws).
    4. **Exceptions**: Interns and temporary staff are not eligible unless explicitly approved by the CTO (e.g., for critical projects).
    
    For questions, contact **People Operations (people-ops@novaai.com)** or refer to the **On-Call Policy** in the internal wiki (linked [here](https://wiki.novaai.com/on-call-policy)).
